                            <comment id="463958" author="adilger" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2025 23:58:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems likely that this is caused by the same issue as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19181&quot; title=&quot;interop sanity test_56wc: file data has changed (1): md5sum invalid argument&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19181&quot;&gt;LU-19181&lt;/a&gt;, since they are both interop issues with older servers that started at the same time, and related to &quot;dd&quot; or other tool reading the file. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are similar failures in sanity test_44f, test_56wc, test_101d, test_133e, test_150bb, but I can&apos;t see what operation is common between those subtests vs. ones that are passing. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Message on the client console reports the same error on all failed subtests:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;LustreError: 6752:0:(osc_request.c:2879:osc_build_rpc()) lustre-OST0004-osc-ffff93064215c000: prep_req failed: rc = -22
[ 4042.852345] LustreError: 6752:0:(osc_cache.c:2205:osc_check_rpcs()) Read request failed with -22
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this seems very systematic, since these same subtests are failing 100% since 2025-03-07.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="463944" author="adilger" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2025 22:31:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stancheff&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stancheff&quot;&gt;stancheff&lt;/a&gt; would you be able to take a look at this?  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a 100% interop regression with DIO between master clients and 2.15 servers (5/5 interop failures in the past week). It is not failing with 2.16 servers (5/5 interop pass in the past week).  I don&apos;t think this is a test script issue, because it is just fsx running and not using some new feature (maybe Hybrid IO?).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
